  "text": "Western blot analysis. Western blot analysis of mouse sera was conducted as previously described (77) using a sonicated preparation of B. hermsii or the n-butanol extract of B. hermsii that was prepared as described for B. burgdorferi [CITATION_1] . Briefly, 120 g of B. hermsii sonicate or 12 g protein from the aqueous phase of an n-butanol extraction of B. hermsii was separated on a sodium dodecyl sulfate-12% polyacrylamide gel electrophoresis gel and transferred to an Immobilon-P membrane (Millipore, Bedford, MA). Blots were incubated with a 1/50 dilution of infected or control mouse sera. Bands were detected using alkaline phosphatase (AP)-conjugated goat anti-mouse IgM or AP-conjugated goat antimouse IgG antibodies (Invitrogen). GlpQ and Vsp33 were identified with rabbit antisera [CITATION_2] or mouse monoclonal antibody H4825 (55), respectively.",
